<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Museado — OPAN</title>

    {# reveal.js CSS (base + black theme + highlight) is loaded via the
       @survos/reveal-bundle stimulus controller's importmap autoimport #}

    <style>
        body, html {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            height: 100%;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .reveal {
            width: 100vw;
            height: 100vh;
        }
        .reveal h1, .reveal h2 { text-transform: none; }
        .reveal section img { border: none; box-shadow: 0 0.5em 2em rgba(0,0,0,.4); }
        .reveal .subtitle { color: #9ab; font-size: 0.65em; }
        .reveal .credit { position: absolute; bottom: 0.6em; right: 1em; font-size: 0.35em; color: #789; }
    </style>

    {# Asset Mapper imports #}
    {% block importmap %}
        {{ importmap('app') }}
    {% endblock %}
</head>
<body>
{% set _sc = '@survos/reveal-bundle/reveal' %}

<div class="reveal" {{ stimulus_controller(_sc) }}>
    <div class="slides">

        <section>
            <img src="{{ asset('images/opan-slides/museado-logo.png') }}" style="max-width:60vw; box-shadow:none;">
            <p class="subtitle">1,500 archives — soon to be 10,000</p>
            <p class="subtitle">Built on open source components</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Tools We Build/Use</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Fast, federated search</li>
                <li>Timeline</li>
                <li>Gallery</li>
                <li>Chatbots</li>
                <li>AI captions &amp; tagging</li>
                <li>IIIF, ARK, EXIF/resizing, find faces</li>
                <li>Documents &amp; PhotoStory</li>
                <li>Oral history &amp; interviews</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section data-background-image="{{ asset('images/opan-slides/fortepan-fpeu-working.jpeg') }}" data-background-size="contain" data-background-color="#111">
            <h2 style="background:rgba(0,0,0,.55); display:inline-block; padding:0.2em 0.4em;">Fast, typo-tolerant, federated search</h2>
            <p class="subtitle" style="background:rgba(0,0,0,.55); display:inline-block; padding:0.2em 0.4em;">
                Live: <a href="https://museado.org/meili/folio-set/fortepan" target="_blank" style="color:#9ab;">museado.org/meili/folio-set/fortepan</a>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section data-background-image="{{ asset('images/opan-slides/zm-home-foliosets.jpeg') }}" data-background-size="contain" data-background-color="#111">
            <h2 style="background:rgba(0,0,0,.55); display:inline-block; padding:0.2em 0.4em;">898,589 items. One search box.</h2>
            <p class="subtitle" style="background:rgba(0,0,0,.55); display:inline-block; padding:0.2em 0.4em;">"Meet the Scholar" — ask questions about any photo, in any language</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>3,411 collections. 898,589 items. 9 providers.</h2>
            <p class="subtitle">Diverse data means diverse experience:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Multiple languages</li>
                <li>Multiple modes — audio, photos, PDFs, and (recently) video</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Tools you should know</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Timeline</li>
                <li>Gallery</li>
                <li>Chatbots</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Infrastructure, under the hood</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>IIIF</li>
                <li>ARK identifiers</li>
                <li>EXIF / metadata / resizing</li>
                <li>Find faces</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Beyond photos</h2>
            <p class="subtitle">Documents can enrich a PhotoStory</p>
            <p>Fortepan's FotoStory tools</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>ScanStation</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Photo &amp; metadata ingest</li>
                <li>Optionally integrated with auto-tagging &amp; captioning</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:1.2em;">
                <div style="flex:1; text-align:left;">
                    <h2>AI fills in the gaps</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Captions for undescribed photos</li>
                        <li>Tags &amp; topics, automatically</li>
                        <li>Never overwrites your own metadata</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div style="flex:1;">
                    <img src="{{ asset('images/opan-slides/zoomed.png') }}" style="max-height:70vh; max-width:100%;">
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>New: oral history &amp; interviews</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Audio with a synchronized transcript</li>
                <li>Searchable right alongside your photos</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="subtitle">
                {# TODO: paste the real YouTube links here #}
                <a href="#" style="color:#9ab;">Jews in Mexico</a> &middot;
                <a href="#" style="color:#9ab;">Slave Voices</a>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h1>Let's build this together</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">I know OPAN is about photos — I wanted to share these tools (documents, interviews, and more) just so you know they exist.</p>
            <p class="subtitle">Tac Tacelosky &middot; Museado</p>
        </section>

    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
